'''Forestation''' is the establishment of [[forest]] growth on areas that either had forest or lacked it naturally.<ref>Nyland, R.D. ''Silviculture: Concepts and Applications''. 3rd ed. 2016. p. 67. [https://books.google.com/books?id=qDypDAAAQBAJ&lpg=PR1&hl=&pg=PA67#v=onepage&q&f=false link].</ref> In the first case, the process is called [[reforestation]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dictionaryofforestry.org/dict/term/reforestation |title=SAFnet Dictionary &#124; Definition For [reforestation&#93; |publisher=Dictionaryofforestry.org |date=2008-08-13 |accessdate=2012-02-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314232006/http://dictionaryofforestry.org/dict/term/reforestation |archivedate=2012-03-14 |df= }}</ref> while the second is called [[afforestation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dictionaryofforestry.org/dict/term/afforestation |title=SAFnet Dictionary &#124; Definition For [afforestation&#93; |publisher=Dictionaryofforestry.org |date=2008-10-23 |accessdate=2012-02-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314232003/http://dictionaryofforestry.org/dict/term/afforestation |archivedate=2012-03-14 }}</ref> 

