'''HEPBS''' ('''N-(2-Hydroxyethyl)piperazine-N'-(4-butanesulfonic acid)''') is a [[zwitterionic]] organic chemical [[buffering agent]]; one of [[Good's buffer]]s. HEPBS and [[HEPES]] have very similar structures and properties, HEPBS also having a [[pH]] in the physiological range (7.6-9.0 useful range). This makes it possible to use it for [[cell culture]] work.
