The '''Siberian Nuclear Power Plant''' ('''Sibirskaya Nuclear Power Plant''') was built in the city of [[Seversk]] (then known as Tomsk-7), [[Tomsk Oblast]]. It was the second nuclear power plant in the USSR and the first industrial-scale nuclear power plant in the country ([[Obninsk Nuclear Power Plant|the first NPP]], built in [[Obninsk]], had a capacity of only 6 MW).
