A '''whip''' is a slender, unbranched [[shoot]] or [[plant]].<ref>https://www.telegraph.co.uk/gardening/3324510/Get-your-whips-into-shape.html</ref>  This term is used in [[forestry]] to refer to unbranched young [[tree]] [[seedling]]s of approximately 0.5-1.0 m (1&nbsp;ft 7 in-3&nbsp;ft 3 in) in height and 2–3 years old that have been grown for planting out.

